The paper deals with missing data imputation using deep generative models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper compares and proposes improvements to existing methodologies for missing data imputation using deep generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of machine learning. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible sub-categories, as they are relevant to the use of deep generative models and handling missing data in datasets.
